## 1. Off-grid Design Philosophy

- Treat off-grid capability as resilience planning, not as a promise of full autonomy.
- Prioritize life-safety, frost protection, monitoring, water pressure, limited lighting, communications, and safe shutdown before comfort or amenity loads.
- Keep all assumptions visible so licensed professionals can replace placeholders with engineered values.

## 2. Grid-connected Versus Off-grid Modes

- Grid-connected mode may support normal loads, battery charging, monitoring, and export/import if permitted by the utility.
- Off-grid/islanded mode should be limited to defined critical loads unless engineered otherwise.
- Transfer switching, anti-islanding, earthing/neutral handling, protection coordination, and grid approval are TBD by licensed professionals.

