## 10. Winter Solar Risk

- Winter performance is the major risk for a mountain cabin: snow cover, low sun angle, short days, cold equipment, fog, shading, and limited access can sharply reduce PV production.
- Battery capacity and charging/discharging capability may be reduced in cold conditions unless equipment is installed in a suitable protected environment.
- The system must include conservative winter operation modes and must not promise full off-grid autonomy.

## 11. Generator Runtime Concept

- Generator runtime is a planning topic only and depends on real loads, fuel capacity, altitude derating, maintenance, start reliability, noise restrictions, and weather access.
- Generator operation should focus on battery charging, water system support, frost protection, and critical loads before comfort loads.
- Fuel storage, exhaust safety, CO risk, ventilation, grounding/neutral treatment, and transfer equipment require professional design.

## 12. Water Storage

- Water storage placeholder: {{ off_grid.water_tank_l }} L.
- Storage may improve resilience but does not guarantee water independence because pumps, filters, freezing risk, water quality, refill logistics, access, and maintenance remain constraints.
- Tank location, overflow, venting, cleaning access, structural support, drain-down, and frost protection require plumbing/mechanical review.

