## 14. Internet Connectivity

- Internet connectivity supports monitoring, alerts, remote access, weather data, solar/battery notifications, and maintenance visibility.
- Local-first operation must remain available during internet outages.
- Cellular, satellite, or secondary WAN failover can be considered, but no provider availability or uptime is guaranteed.

## 15. Emergency Modes

- Critical-load mode: preserve heating controls, pumps, monitoring, refrigerator/freezer, limited lighting, communications, and alarms.
- Low-battery mode: disable DHW boost, laundry, terrace comfort loads, exterior amenities, and discretionary outlets.
- Generator-fault mode: reduce to minimum frost/safety loads and alert owner/service provider.
- Winter-vacancy mode: combine low setpoints, freeze monitoring, leak detection, UPS-backed network, and manual inspection plan.

## 16. Maintenance Schedule

- Monthly/seasonal: inspect PV surface access, visible wiring, inverter/battery status, generator readiness, fuel condition, water tank/pump status, and network alerts.
- Before winter: test generator start/transfer sequence, verify battery reserve settings, check heating/frost protection, clean gutters/drainage, and confirm remote monitoring.
- After outages/faults: record battery state, generator runtime, alarms, load shedding, water system status, and corrective actions.
- Annual: licensed professional review of PV, battery, inverter, generator, protection devices, water storage, and wastewater equipment.

